<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-12T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-12T19:00:00-05:00" n="720" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.6363/10–344: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-12T20:00:00-04:00">October
                                    12, 1944—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1080. Reurtel no. 1519 of Sept. 20 and no. 1580, Oct, 3.<note n="73" xml:id="d720fn73">Neither printed.</note> As result of consideration
                            by the Essential Requirements Committee,<note n="74" xml:id="d720fn74">Presumably the Requirements Committee of the War Production
                                Board.</note> the following total quantities for Chile covering the
                            12 months’ period beginning October 1 are approved as follows in
                                barrels:<note n="75" xml:id="d720fn75">These figures represent an
                                increase of 33,838 barrels of gasoline and 22,499 barrels of
                                kerosene.</note>
                            <table cols="2" rend="width: 50%" rendition="#center-block" rows="5">
                                <row>
                                    <cell>Gasoline</cell>
                                    <cell role="num">627,138</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>Kerosene</cell>
                                    <cell role="num">102,199</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>Light Diesel oil</cell>
                                    <cell role="num">150,000</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>Heavy Diesel oil</cell>
                                    <cell role="num">195,350</cell>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <cell>Fuel oil</cell>
                                    <cell role="num">5,720,756</cell>
                                </row>
                            </table>
                        </p>
                        <p>Due to mounting war demands for gasoline in the Pacific, the supply
                            situation will not permit any greater supply of gasoline for Chile at
                            this time.</p>
                        <p>The Embassy should submit detailed schedules supporting the above total
                            quantities as soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>